<title>FRANCE: HORSE RACING-FRENCH 1,000 GUINEAS TRIAL RESULT.</title>
<headline>HORSE RACING-FRENCH 1,000 GUINEAS TRIAL RESULT.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-04-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Result of a French 1,000 Guineas</p>
<p>trial, the Prix de la Grotte, a group three race for</p>
<p>three-year-old fillies run over one mile (1.6 kms) at Longchamp</p>
<p>on Sunday:</p>
<p> 1. Always Loyal	(ridden by Freddie Head)</p>
<p> 2. Mousse Glacee     (Vincent Vion)</p>
<p> 3. Green Lady	  (Thierry Jarnet)</p>
<p> 4 Spring Dance	 (Sylvain Guillot)</p>
<p>Five ran.</p>
<p>Distances: A head, half-a-length, two-and-a-half lengths.</p>
<p>Winner owned by Maktoum al Maktoum and trained in France by</p>
<p>Criquette Head.</p>
<p>Value to the winner: $41,481 dollars</p>
<p>Pari-Mutuel (includes a one-franc stake): Win 2.50; (coupled</p>
<p>with Green Lady); Places 1.50, 1.20. SF 7.00.</p>
<p>Prix Greffulhe, a group two French Derby trial for</p>
<p>three-year-old colts and fillies run over 2.1-km:</p>
<p> 1. Peintre Celebre   (Olivier Peslier)</p>
<p> 2. Astarabad	   (Gerald Mosse)</p>
<p> 3. Kashwan	     (Thierry Thulliez)</p>
<p> 4. New Frontier	(Thierry Jarnet)</p>
<p>Six ran.</p>
<p>Distances: Two lengths, a nose, two-and-a-half lengths.</p>
<p>Winner owned by Daniel Wildenstein and trained in France by</p>
<p>Andre Fabre.</p>
<p>Value to the winner: $60,006</p>
<p>Pari-Mutuel: Win 3.40; places 1.40, 1.20. Straight Forecast</p>
<p>9.90.</p>
<p>Prix de Fontainebleau, a French 2,000 Guineas group three</p>
<p>trial for three-year-old colts run over one mile (1.6 kms):</p>
<p> 1. Daylami	  (Gerald Mosse)</p>
<p> 2. Loup Sauvage   (Olivier Peslier)</p>
<p> 3. Fine Fellow    (Guy Guignard)</p>
<p> 4. Majorien	 (Freddie Head)</p>
<p>Six ran.</p>
<p>Distances: Two lengths, a short head, two lengths.</p>
<p>Winner owned by the Aga Khan and trained in France by Alain</p>
<p>de Royer-Dupre.</p>
<p>Value to the winner: $41,481</p>
<p>Pari-Mutuel: Win 3.00; places 1.80, 2.20. Straight Forecast</p>
<p>16.60.</p>
</text>
